a clean and cost-effective alternative to traditional fuels such as coal and oil. The industrial sector is increasingly adopting biomass fuels, including white wood pellets, to comply with environmental regulations and reduce operational costs associated with conventional fuels. White wood pellets are especially popular in industries where consistent and high-temperature heat is required, including ceramics, cement production, and steel manufacturing.</p><p>Moreover, the advantages of white wood pellets in industrial furnaces extend beyond just environmental benefits. These pellets are known for their high calorific value, which ensures that industrial processes requiring sustained heat can continue efficiently without interruptions. The ability to achieve high temperatures without producing excess emissions is a major driving factor for their adoption in industrial furnaces. As industries become more aware of the economic and environmental advantages of using biomass fuels, the demand for white wood pellets in this sector is expected to grow steadily in the coming years.</p><h2>Civil Use</h2><p>White wood pellets are also increasingly used in civil applications, particularly in residential heating and small-scale commercial uses. In this segment, the pellets are primarily employed in pellet stoves and boilers, offering an environmentally friendly heating solution that is both affordable and efficient. With growing consumer awareness of environmental issues and the desire to reduce energy costs, white wood pellets have gained popularity as a clean alternative to traditional heating methods such as oil or gas. These pellets are easy to store, transport, and use, making them a preferred choice for households and small businesses seeking sustainable heating options.</p><p>The civil use of white wood pellets is supported by various government incentives and subsidies aimed at promoting renewable heating solutions. Many regions are adopting policies that encourage the tr